cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Myco in research or a derived substrate, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Myco — Agent-First Symbiotic Cognitive Substrate"
abstract: >-
  Myco is a long-lived, self-validating cognitive substrate designed exclusively
  for LLM agents. Twenty manifest-driven verbs (germinate / hunger / eat /
  sense / forage / assimilate / digest / sporulate / traverse / propagate /
  immune / senesce / fruit / molt / winnow / ramify / graft / intake / excrete
  / brief) compose the ingest → digest → circulate → self-check → evolve life
  cycle. Forty-seven lint dimensions enforce contract invariants (R1–R7)
  mechanically, including atomic-write R6 enforcement, LLM-provider boundary
  (MP1/MP2/MP3), and graph connectedness (SE1/SE3/CG1/CG2). The kernel
  itself is a substrate — editable by default — so the agent that maintains
  Myco is the same agent that uses it.
